his
complex
nature
lay
a
rich
vein
of
sensualism,
at
the
sport
of
which
he
placed
all
the
prizes
of
his
life.
The
eye,
the
ear,
the
touch,
the
palate,
all
were
his
masters.
The
bouquet
of
old
vintages,
the
scent
of
rare
exotics,
the
curves
and
tints
of
the
daintiest
