of
rain
tinkled
on
the
glass
with
each
fresh
sough
of
the
gale,
drowning
for
the
instant
the
dull
gurgle
and
drip
from
the
eaves.
Douglas
Stone
had
finished
his
dinner,
and
sat
by
his
fire
in
the
study,
a
glass
of
rich
